    {
      "id": 1,
      "question": "What is the difference between the Internet and the Web?",
      "preferredAnswer": "The **Internet** is the global network of connected computers. The **Web (WWW)** is a collection of websites and web pages that run on top of the Internet. The Internet is the infrastructure; the Web is a service that uses it."
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "question": "Explain the request-response cycle in simple terms.",
      "preferredAnswer": "When you type a URL in your browser, the browser sends a **request** to the server asking for the web page. The server finds the HTML file and sends it back as a **response**. The browser then reads the HTML and displays the page on your screen."
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "question": "Why is HTML not considered a programming language?",
      "preferredAnswer": "HTML is a **markup language**, not a programming language. It has no logic, no conditions (if/else), no loops, and no variables. It only **describes the structure** of content — it tells the browser *what* things are, not *how to think or decide*."
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "question": "Write the basic structure of an HTML document and label each part.",
      "preferredAnswer": "```html\n<!DOCTYPE html>        <!-- Declaration: tells browser this is HTML5 -->\n<html>                 <!-- Root element -->\n  <head>               <!-- Head: metadata, title, links -->\n    <title>Page Title</title>\n  </head>\n  <body>               <!-- Body: all visible content -->\n    <h1>Heading</h1>\n    <p>Paragraph</p>\n  </body>\n</html>\n```"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "question": "What is the difference between an opening tag, closing tag, and a self-closing tag? Give one example of each.",
      "preferredAnswer": "- **Opening tag:** Starts an element → `<p>`\n- **Closing tag:** Ends an element (has `/`) → `</p>`\n- **Self-closing tag:** Has no closing tag and no content → `<br>`\n\nExample: `<p>Hello</p>` uses opening and closing tags. `<br>` is self-closing."
    }
